This repository doesn't contain a full application. Instead, it holds small, reusable, self-contained pieces of the UI. This practice ensures a consistent look and feel across larger applications.

Purpose: Store and manage reusable UI components like buttons and displays.

Contents: Separate folders for each component (e.g., /timer-display, /reset-button).

Example Component: /timer-display

timer.html:
<div class="timer-component">00:00:00</div>
timer.css:
.timer-component {
    font-size: 1.5em;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: #007bff;
    font-family: monospace;
}
timer.js (A simple class to manage its state):
class TimerDisplay {
    constructor(element) {
        this.element = element;
    }
    update(timeString) {
        this.element.textContent = timeString;
    }
}
